Your second-to-last rule, acceptRoot, is accepting almost everything,  
which overrides any previous rejects. For example, the acceptRoot  
rule would match:

http://www.foo.com/
http://one.two.three.four/dir1/dir2/dir3/

And so on. Since you only seem interested in one domain, you can  
alter the acceptRoot decide rule&#39;s regex to include the full site  
like you did with the rejectNonHtml rule.

However, you might have better luck all around using the  
ContentTypeMatchesRegExpDecideRule.

-Paul


